    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Baccharis venosa are its anti-inflammatory effects, which are attributed to the presence of flavonoids and terpenoids in the plant. The antioxidant activity of Baccharis venosa is responsible for its ability to protect against cell damage and oxidative stress, while its antimicrobial properties allow it to inhibit the growth of various microorganisms, including bacteria and fungi. The plant's antiviral properties, which are mediated by the action of saponins and volatile oils, enable it to inhibit the replication of certain viruses. Baccharis venosa also possesses hepatoprotective properties, which are thought to be due to the antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities of its bioactive compounds. The analgesic and antipyretic effects of Baccharis venosa are attributed to the action of its flavonoids and terpenoids, which can help to reduce pain and fever.",
