    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Baccharis venosa are flavonoids, including quercetin and kaempferol, which have anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties, and phenolic acids such as ellagic and ferulic acid, which have antimicrobial and antitumor activities. The plant also contains essential oils, particularly limonene, beta-pinene, and beta-caryophyllene, which have analgesic and anti-inflammatory effects. In addition, Baccharis venosa contains terpenoids, including ursolic acid and oleanolic acid, which have anti-inflammatory and immunomodulatory properties. The plant's flavonoids and phenolic acids also exhibit antimicrobial and antiviral activities, making it useful for treating infections and promoting wound healing. The combination of these bioactive compounds contributes to Baccharis venosa's traditional uses for treating a range of health conditions, including inflammation, infections, and cancer.",
