    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Baccharis venosa are used for its medicinal properties and include tea, an aqueous solution made by infusing the leaves in hot water to treat digestive issues, infusions, a liquid extract made by steeping the leaves in cold water for fever reduction, tincture, a concentrated liquid solution prepared by soaking the leaves in a solvent like ethanol to treat respiratory problems, and decoction, a strong liquid extract made by boiling the leaves in water to treat skin irritations and salve, a topical application made by infusing the leaves in oil to treat wounds and skin conditions. Baccharis venosa has been traditionally used for its anti-inflammatory, antibacterial, and antifungal properties. The tea and infusion preparations are used for their diuretic and expectorant properties, while the tincture is used for its sedative effects. Decoction and salve preparations are used for their wound-healing and anti-inflammatory properties. The herbal preparations of Baccharis venosa are also used to treat respiratory issues, such as bronchitis and asthma.",
